Organization = {IEEE Reg 10; IEEE Bangladesh Sect},
Abstract = {In this modern, technological age, the internet has been adopted by the
   masses. And with it, the danger of malicious attacks by cybercriminals
   have increased. These attacks are done via Malware, and have resulted in
   billions of dollars of financial damage. This makes the prevention of
   malicious attacks an essential part of the battle against cybercrime. In
   this paper, we are applying machine learning algorithms to predict the
   malware infection rates of computers based on its features. We are using
   supervised machine learning algorithms and gradient boosting algorithms.
   We have collected a publicly available dataset, which was divided into
   two parts, one being the training set, and the other will be the testing
   set. After conducting four different experiments using the
   aforementioned algorithms, it has been discovered that LightGBM is the
   best model with an AUC Score of 0.73926.},
