   Cryptography Engineering (SPACE), IIT Kharagpur, ELECTR NETWORK, DEC
   10-13, 2021},
Abstract = {The amount of Internet traffic is ever increasing. With a well
   maintained network infrastructure, people find their way to Internet
   forums, video streaming services, social media and webshops on a
   day-to-day basis. With the growth of the online world, criminal
   activities have also spread out to the Internet. Security researchers
   and system administrators develop and maintain infrastructures to
   control these possible threats. This work focuses on one aspect of
   network security: intrusion detection. An Intrusion Detection System
   (IDS) is only one of the many components in the security engineer's
   toolbox. An IDS is a passive component that tries to detect malicious
   activities. With the increase of Internet traffic and bandwidth, the
   detection speed of IDSs needs to be improved accordingly. This work
   focuses on how Field-programmable Gate Arrays (FPGA) are used as
   hardware accelerators to assist the IDS in keeping up with high network
   speed. We give an overview of three approaches: Intrusion detection
   based on machine learning, pattern matching, and large flow detection.
   This work is concluded with a comparison between the three approaches on
   the most relevant metrics.},
