Abstract = {Even now that DNA test has become common, latent fingerprints are still
   a useful evidence for finding criminals. However, the latent
   fingerprints are often damaged and overlapped with each other. At
   present, these overlapped fingerprints are separated manually by a
   person. It is not only time-consuming task, but also less likely to be
   adopted as evidence because it is difficult to rule out of the intention
   of a person. In this paper, non-destructive method to capture and
   separate overlapped fingerprints using digital holography and machine
   learning is presented and demonstrated.},
