   surveillance is required to construct a facial attribute, a visual
   likeness of a victim's face. Many researchers have contributed their
   work in this field by using various methods. Real time face detection is
   still a tedious task and achieve a good performance of the system. In
   this paper we will compare two models of face recognition. First is
