Organization = {Agnel Charities Fr C Rodrigues Inst Technol; IEEE; IEEE Bombay Sect;
   Comp Soc India; Indian Soc Tech Educ; CSIR; Indian Soc Heating
   Regrigerationing Engineers; Inst Elect \& Telecommunicat; Tata
   Consultancy Serv; BRNS},
Abstract = {The growing crime rate of any country is always one of the biggest
   obstacles to its growth and development. With more manpower it certainly
   helps to keep the crime rate at bay, but is manpower the ideal solution?
   No. This may come as a surprise that despite Big Data being the boom of
   the century is yet to take firm roots when it comes to helping solve a
   Criminal Investigation. With the aim of changing this, our paper
   describes the need of a system which analyzes the Call Data Records
   (CDR) using Big Data technology. Our proposed idea through this research
   paper is to develop a system which takes as input mobile number/s and
   extracts corresponding CDRs, thereby generating multiple databases of
   CDRs. After this it analyzes these databases and finds various links
   between various suspects (mobile numbers) and generates as output,
   conclusions of its analysis. This conclusion may consist of phone
   numbers, call durations, locations etc. With proper analysis of the CDRs
   of the various suspects, the Anti - Crime team can move forward on
   multiple fronts simultaneously.},
