   INFORMATION TECHNOLOGY (AMEIT 2015)},
Year = {2015},
Pages = {817-824},
Note = {International Conference on Advances in Management Engineering and
   Information Technology (AMEIT), Bangkok, THAILAND, JUN 28-29, 2015},
Abstract = {The first results of the third phase of the research project that aims
   to detect crime patterns with data mining techniques in the Crime
   Observatory of the Municipality of Pasto (Colombia), using the CRISP-DM
   methodology, is presented. From a datamart, built in the second phase of
   this project, a classification model based on decision trees, which
   allows discovering crime patterns of deaths from external causes, was
   built. In this datamart; historic, clean, and transformed information on
   fatal and nonfatal injuries from external causes registered in the Crime
   Observatory for 11-year period is stored. The knowledge generated will
   help the government and security agencies to make effective decisions in
   relation to the implementation of crime prevention plans and public
   safety.},
