   ELECTR NETWORK, APR 12-14, 2022},
Abstract = {Healthcare organizations are a popular target for cybercrime due to its
   critical and vulnerable infrastructure. The IT threat detection system
   (ITDS), described in this work, is an intelligent system that improves
   the incident detection by providing network monitoring and intrusion
   detection by means of a machine learning approach. Different machine
   learning techniques were studied in public datasets, and then fine-tuned
   with healthcare data. Thus, the main contribution of this work is a plug
   and play toolkit built for hospitals and which allow them to detect
   security events. Another relevant outcome of this work is a ``real{''}
   hospital ecosystem that allows the simulation and test of security tools
   in a hospital environment without sacrificing its availability.},
