Abstract = {Evidence-based management is a popular contemporary account of the
   relationship between research and practice in management studies and
   also a powerful paradigm to meet the challenge of big data era by
   linking scientific evidence, organizational facts and expertise judgment
   together. It is emerging in response to heightened demands for public
   accountability and organizational performance. This article defines
   evidence-based management and reviews its origins in the health care and
   business sectors and its recent incorporation into public service. A
   case study is presented to describe the efforts of public service
   agencies to use evidence-based management to improve the performance of
   its crime prevention programs. Consideration is also given to the
   implications of evidence-based management for public service agency
   practice and public management in the era of big data.},
