   Engineers Genoa; European Federat Med Informat},
Abstract = {Due to the specific circumstances related to the COVID-19 pandemic, many
   countries have enforced emergency measures such as self-isolation and
   restriction of movement and assembly, which are also directly affecting
   the functioning of their respective public health and judicial systems.
   The goal of this study is to identify the efficiency of the criminal
   sanctions in Russia that were introduced in the beginning of COVID-19
   outbreak using machine learning methods. We have developed a regression
   model for the fine handed out, using random forest regression and
   XGBoost regression, and calculated the features importance parameters.
   We have developed classification models for the remission of the penalty
   and for setting a sentence using a gradient boosting classifier.},
